1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,176
Resolvamos en tres pasos.

2
00:00:01,176 --> 00:00:02,353
La función signo $sgn(x)$

3
00:00:02,353 --> 00:00:03,529
vale 1 si $x>0$,

4
00:00:03,529 --> 00:00:04,706
-1 si $x<0$ y

5
00:00:04,706 --> 00:00:05,882
0 si. Aplicamos la

6
00:00:05,882 --> 00:00:07,059
operación clave y verificamos

7
00:00:07,059 --> 00:00:08,235
el resultado. El límite

8
00:00:08,235 --> 00:00:09,412
izquierdo es -1 y

9
00:00:09,412 --> 00:00:10,588
el derecho es 1.

10
00:00:10,588 --> 00:00:11,765
Al no ser iguales,

11
00:00:11,765 --> 00:00:12,941
el límite no existe.

12
00:00:12,941 --> 00:00:14,118
Hay un salto brusco.

13
00:00:14,118 --> 00:00:15,000
Respuesta final confirmada.
